# Questions

# 1. What is my project about?

I built an AI system that analyzes NASA Kepler exoplanet data using machine learning to find hidden patterns, clusters, and anomalies in space signals.

# 2. Why did i choose this project?

I chose this project because I’m interested in AI and space science, and I wanted to explore how machine learning can be used in real astrophysical data analysis instead of simple classroom datasets.

# 3. What dataset did i use?

I used NASA Kepler TCE dataset which contains over 34,000 exoplanet signal observations with 113 features.

# 4. Why did i use unsupervised learning?

I used unsupervised learning because the dataset has no labels. We don’t know which signals are confirmed planets, so the model has to find patterns on its own.

# 5. What clustering algorithm did i use and why?

I used KMeans because it helps divide data into meaningful groups based on similarity. I also used DBSCAN because it can detect natural clusters and noise without predefining the number of clusters.

# 6. What is Isolation Forest used for?

I used Isolation Forest for anomaly detection. It helps identify rare or unusual signals that do not match the general pattern of the dataset.

# 7. What is PCA and why did i use it?

PCA reduces high-dimensional data into 2D so we can visualize hidden structure and clusters in a simple way.


# 8. What insight did i get from the dataset?

I found that exoplanet signals are not random — they form structured clusters based mainly on orbital period, and a small portion of signals are extreme anomalies.

# 9. How do i know my clustering is valid?

I evaluated clustering using silhouette score and also visually checked PCA plots. The clusters showed meaningful separation and consistent patterns.

# 10. What challenges did i face?

The dataset was very large, noisy, and had skewed distributions. I had to carefully clean, scale, and transform the data before applying machine learning.

# 11. If i improve this project, what would i do?

I would:

Add deep learning models for anomaly detection
Build a 3D orbital simulation
Use real-time NASA API data
Improve dashboard interactivity
